kenticocommunity.qandaanswerdata.QAndAAnswerDataContent:
I think you can use [WorkspaceInfo](https://api-reference.kentico.com/api/CMS.Workspaces.WorkspaceInfo.html) directly - a workspace is just a logical container that a content item, smart folder, or content folder is associated with.

```CSharp
public class MyService(IInfoProvider<WorkspaceInfo> provider)
{
  private reasonly IInfoProvider<WorkspaceInfo> provider = provider;

  public Task CreateWorkspace(...)
  {
    var newWorkspace = new WorkspaceInfo()
    {
      WorkspaceName = "...",
      DisplayName = "..."
    };

    await provider.SetAsync(newWorkspace);
  }
}
```
